    {
      "name": "NEWOBJ",
      "description": "New object",
      "help": "New object (NEWOBJ)\n\nSpecifies the new name of the object to be renamed. The object remains in the same library.\n\nThis is a required parameter.",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": true,
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "positional": 3,
      "placeholder": "NEWOBJ",
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "ASPDEV",
      "description": "ASP device",
      "help": "ASP device (ASPDEV)\n\nSpecifies the auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name where storage is allocated for the library containing the object to be renamed. If the library is in an ASP that is not part of the thread's library name space, this parameter must be specified to ensure the correct object is renamed. If a library to be renamed is in an auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device that is not currently part of the thread's library name space, specify the library as OBJ(QSYS/name), the object type as OBJTYPE(*LIB), and the ASP device as ASPDEV(name).\n\nNote: ASPDEV(*) is the only valid value when *LIBL or *CURLIB is specified for the library (qualifier 2) of the Object (OBJ) parameter.\n\nNote: To specify a specific auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name, you must have use (*USE) authority for each ASP device in the ASP group.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *, *CURASPGRP, *SYSBAS",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "placeholder": "*",
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "SYSTEM",
      "description": "System",
      "help": "System (SYSTEM)\n\nSpecifies if the rename is to be done on the local system or on a remote system, if the file is a Distributed Data Management (DDM) file.\n\nNote: If you want to rename a remote file, two DDM files must be used. The existing DDM file is specified for the Object (OBJ) parameter, and the new DDM file is specified for the New object (NEWOBJ) parameter. The new DDM file must be in the same library as the existing DDM file. When the remote rename occurs, it is the remote file name in the existing DDM file that is renamed to the new DDM file name.",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*LCL",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*LCL",
          "value": "*LCL"
        },
        {
          "label": "*RMT",
          "value": "*RMT"
        },
        {
          "label": "*FILETYPE",
          "value": "*FILETYPE"
        }
      ],
      "positional": 4
    }
  ],
  "examples": [
    {
      "code": "RNMOBJ OBJ(PAYROLL/FILEX) OBJTYPE(*FILE) NEWOBJ(MSTR)"
    }
  ],
